---
description: Commit-ready code generation rules
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Generated code should be commit-ready.

Rules:
- write code that can be committed with minimal manual cleanup
- avoid tutorial commentary in code
- avoid fake sample data unless explicitly requested
- include only comments that clarify intent
- use realistic types and edge handling
- prefer complete small implementations over broad shallow scaffolds

When asked to implement:
- complete the requested slice end-to-end where feasible
- wire the main flow, not just type definitions
- keep future extensibility without over-engineering